# 🏦 Banking Transactions API - Sample Requests
# Use this file with the VS Code REST Client extension to test the API endpoints.

@host = http://localhost:3000

###
# 1. List All Transactions
# Returns all transactions in the system.
GET {{host}}/transactions

###
# 2. Filter Transactions by Account
# Returns transactions associated with the given account.
GET {{host}}/transactions?accountId=ACC-12345

###
# 3. Filter Transactions by Type
# Returns only transfer transactions.
GET {{host}}/transactions?type=transfer

###
# 4. Filter Transactions by Date Range
# Returns transactions within the specified date range.
GET {{host}}/transactions?from=2026-06-01&to=2026-06-30

###
# 5. Combined Filters
# Returns transfers involving ACC-12345 within the date range.
GET {{host}}/transactions?accountId=ACC-12345&type=transfer&from=2026-06-01&to=2026-06-30


###
# 6. Create a Transfer Transaction
# Moves money from one account to another.
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "toAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": 150.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "transfer"
}

###
# 7. Create a Deposit Transaction
# Adds money to an account (no fromAccount needed).
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "amount": 500.50,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "type": "deposit"
}

###
# 8. Create a Withdrawal Transaction
# Deducts money from an account (no toAccount needed).
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": 75.25,
  "currency": "GBP",
  "type": "withdrawal"
}


###
# 9. Get Transaction by ID
# Replace the ID below with an actual transaction ID from the list.
GET {{host}}/transactions/5900902f-5951-418c-a314-8beff36adf93


###
# 10. Get Account Balance
# Computes the current balance of the account.
GET {{host}}/accounts/ACC-12345/balance


###
# 11. Get Account Summary (Task 4 Option A)
# Computes aggregate statistics of deposit/withdrawal totals.
GET {{host}}/accounts/ACC-12345/summary


###
# ==========================================
# 🛑 VALIDATION & ERROR HANDLING TESTS
# ==========================================

###
# Error: Invalid Account Code Format (Pattern mismatch)
# Accounts must follow the ACC-XXXXX format.
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-INVALID123",
  "toAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "transfer"
}

###
# Error: Negative Amount
# Amount must be positive.
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "toAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": -50.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "transfer"
}

###
# Error: Too Many Decimal Places
# Amount cannot exceed 2 decimal places.
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "toAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": 99.999,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "transfer"
}

###
# Error: Unsupported Currency
# Currency must be a valid ISO-4217 code (USD, EUR, GBP, JPY, CAD, AUD, etc.)
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "toAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "FGY",
  "type": "transfer"
}

###
# Error: Non-existent Transaction ID (404 Not Found)
GET {{host}}/transactions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###
# Error: Account with No History (404 Not Found)
GET {{host}}/accounts/ACC-99999/balance
